						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What's wrong with the Famitracker or Nerdtracker drivers?  I haven't used Famitracker as much so I am actually pretty curious.</div><br />How much RAM and how much of an NROM-128 does it use? I seem to remember NT2 taking 3 KiB <em>without</em> sound effect support, compared to my own 1 KiB sound driver (used in LJ65 and Concentration Room) that has sound effect support but no "effects" channel.<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Yeah, 3kB sounds about right.  The data size is more important (and yeah NT2's NED files can compress a lot further - like MatrixZ's NESnake did).  I figure I would reserve at least 16kB for music code/data, probably more though.  With uncompressed NED's that's not a heck of a lot of music (Solar Wars' soundtrack was 16kB, not counting the DPCM samples).</div>

